articles.headline: College football Week 5 live updates: Top plays and games
articles.description: Here are the best plays, moment and reactions from around college football in Week 5.

images.name: Franklin calls Penn State's White Out best environment in college football
images.caption: Head coach James Franklin joins "College GameDay" to discuss Penn State's famous White Out game.

articles.headline: Gordon's 3 touchdowns, Dyson's 2 sacks spur Tulane to 31-14 win over Tulsa
articles.description: Javin Gordon rushed for three touchdowns and Harvey Dyson III had two sacks in Tulane's 31-14 win over Tulsa in the Green Wave's American Athletic Conference season opener on Saturday.

articles.headline: Chambliss' 385 scrimmage yards propels No. 13 Mississippi past No. 4 LSU, 24-19
articles.description: Trinidad Chambliss passed for 314 yards and a touchdown  a third straight 300-yard passing performance for the Division II transfer and No. 13 Mississippi defeated No. 4 LSU 24-19 on Saturday.

images.name: Lane Kiffin relishes Ole Miss avenging last year's loss at LSU
images.caption: Kiffin touches on the Rebels' resilience and the home crowd's atmosphere while emphasizing how great it feels to get revenge from last year's loss to the Tigers in Baton Rouge.

articles.headline: Fagnano passes UConn into position for Freeman's field goal and 20-17 win over Buffalo
articles.description: Joe Fagnano led UConn down the field on a last-minute drive, setting up Chris Freeman for a 44-yard field goal with 11 seconds remaining and the Huskies beat Buffalo 20-17 on Saturday.
